This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.
result.caption: State of Wisconsin vs. James Francis Jr

records.addlTxt:
9:00 a.m.  Court calls case from Ashland, WI via Zoom. Attorney Matthew J Tingstad in court for State of Wisconsin.  Attorney Tyler William Wickman in court for James Francis Jr.   Attorney M. Joseph Rafferty Jr. in court for James Francis Jr.  . Defendant James Francis Jr in court.  Here today for preliminary hearing.  DA calls Sgt. Justin Colassaco to testify.  Court swears in witness.  Direct by DA.  Sgt. Colassaco testifies.  9:07 a.m.  Cross by atty. Wickman.  off record  9:10 a.m.  Atty. Wickman continues cross.  No re-direct.  State has no other witnesses.  Atty. Wickman calls Victim to testify.  D.A. objects.  
9:12 a.m.  Off record in which Court researches case law.  9:30 a.m.  Atty. Wickman withdraws request to call victim.   DA makes statement re: probable cause.  Atty. Wickman makes rebuttal argument.  Court finds probable cause and binds over case.   Court gives DA 30 days to file Information.  DA states he will file same within a week.  Arraignment scheduled for Nov. 7, 2022 at 8:30 a.m.  All parties may appear by Zoom if they wish.  Court adjourned at 9:39 a.m.  wmg
Preliminary hearing on October 13, 2022 at 09:00 am.

8:16 a.m.  Court calls case, cites appearances.  Judge McKnight appears with CR via Zoom from Ashland County.  Attorneys Rafferty and Wickland appear from Atty Rafferty's office via Zoom.  Def appears via phone.  Matthew J. Tingstad appears in person for the State of WI.  Vic appears later in hearing via Zoom.  Per Atty Rafferty, complaint was received, def waives reading.  Wants prelim set.  DA requests $50,000 cash bond and states reasons for request.   Atty Rafferty responds.  Refers to Document #4.  Requests signature bond.  Judge addresses parties.  Court sets $5,000 cash bond with provisions of no contact with alleged victim.  No unsupervised contact with persons under 18 y.o.  Bond to be posted by noon or def to turn himself in to Iron County Jail.  Court determines T/L for prelim is 20 days.  Advises of ramifications if def doesn't post bond by noon.  Prelim to be 1 hour long and set for 10/13 at 9:00 a.m.  Advises parties of ability to appear via Zoom.  Adj.  8:34 a.m.  klr
Defendant shall have no contact with alleged Victim.  Def shall have no unsupervised contact with anyone under the age of 18.
Initial appearance on September 26, 2022 at 08:15 am.
